# mnemo Memory Instructions

<!--
Copy this file to your AI tool's instruction file:
  Claude Code:  CLAUDE.md  (or .claude/CLAUDE.md)
  Codex CLI:    AGENTS.md
  opencode:     AGENTS.md
  Cursor:       .cursorrules
  Copilot:      .github/copilot-instructions.md

Edit the sections below to match your project and preferences.
-->

## Memory: Session Start

At the start of EVERY new session, before doing anything else:

1. Call `memory_search` with query `"project setup decisions conventions preferences"`
2. Call `memory_list` with category `"decision"` to review architectural choices
3. Call `note_list` to see recent session notes
4. Briefly summarize what you recalled (2-3 sentences max)

> If mnemo is unavailable, proceed normally and note that memory is offline.

## Memory: What to Save

### Use `memory_save` for facts you want to recall later

| Category | When to use | Example key / value |
|----------|-------------|---------------------|
| `decision` | Architectural or design choices | `auth_strategy` / `"JWT with refresh tokens, no sessions"` |
| `convention` | Coding style or project rules | `error_handling` / `"always wrap with fmt.Errorf, never panic in handlers"` |
| `config` | Environment, tools, endpoints | `db_name` / `"mnemo_prod on localhost:5432"` |
| `bug` | Non-obvious fixes to remember | `sqlite_wal_mode` / `"must enable WAL before first query or FTS5 breaks"` |
| `preference` | How the user likes you to work | `response_style` / `"concise, no summaries at end, code-first"` |

Always set `project` to the current repository name.

### Use `note_save` for longer-form content

- Completed feature summaries
- Post-mortems and retrospectives
- Complex system design documentation
- Research findings

```
note_save(
  project = "<repo-name>",
  title   = "Session 2025-01-15: Auth refactor",
  content = "<what was built, decisions made, open questions>",
  tags    = ["session", "auth", "refactor"]
)
```

## Memory: What NOT to Save

- Temporary debugging output
- Code snippets that already exist in the repo
- Anything that can be derived from `git log` or reading files
- Secrets, passwords, API keys (use a secrets manager)

## Memory: Session End

Before closing a session where significant work happened:

1. Save key decisions made during the session:
   ```
   memory_save(category="decision", key="...", value="...")
   ```

2. Save a session note:
   ```
   note_save(
     title   = "Session YYYY-MM-DD: <topic>",
     content = "## What was done\n...\n## Decisions\n...\n## Next steps\n...",
     tags    = ["session"]
   )
   ```

3. (Optional, if `ENABLE_AUTO_EXTRACT=true`) Call `memory_extract` with a
   plain-text summary of the session to let the AI extract additional facts.

## Memory: Search Tips

- Use `memory_search` with conceptual queries, not exact keywords:
  - ✅ `"how do we handle authentication"`
  - ✅ `"database connection issues"`
  - ❌ `"auth"` (too short, better to use `memory_list category=auth`)

- Use `memory_categories` first if you don't know where to look

- Use `note_search` for longer documents and design docs
